title: Bryce
extract: Origin of the name Bryce: English name originating as a surname taken to English by the French in the Middle Ages. It is believed to be of Celtic origin and might be derived from the element bri (force, strength) or brígh (valor, strength). Var: Bryce. Short: Bri.
